    "question_id" : 11005286,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>When you have a <code>boolean</code> it can be either <code>true</code> or <code>false</code>. Yet when you have a <code>Boolean</code> it can be either <code>Boolean.TRUE</code>, <code>Boolean.FALSE</code> or <code>null</code> as any other object.</p>\n\n<p>In your particular case, your <code>Boolean</code> is <code>null</code> and the <code>if</code> statement triggers an implicit conversion to <code>boolean</code> that produces the <code>NullPointerException</code>. You may need instead:</p>\n\n<pre><code>if(bool != null &amp;&amp; bool) { ... }\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 62111,
      "reputation" : 41273,
      "user_id" : 184730,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 72,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/8ec7cdaaf6fd5ee313cb6228f08cd67c?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "fastcodejava",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/184730/fastcodejava"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 20,
    "last_activity_date" : 1498928205,
    "last_edit_date" : 1498928205,
    "creation_date" : 1339537348,
    "answer_id" : 11005312,
    "question_id" : 11005286,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p><code>Boolean</code> types can be <code>null</code>. You need to do a <code>null</code> check as you have set it to <code>null</code>. </p>\n\n<pre><code>if (bool != null &amp;&amp; bool)\n{\n  //DoSomething\n}                   \n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
