      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "@xtay2 Since you don’t like the idea, please don’t use it. Of course I can prevent a <code>MyTristateBoolean</code> from being <code>null</code>. Ever heard of <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/24/docs/api/java.base/java/util/Objects.html#requireNonNull(T)\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>Objects.requireNonNull()</code></a>? :-) There are also times when I think <code>null</code> was a horrible idea."
